      <p><strong>Quick answer:</strong> The African Grey is the smaller, quieter, far-better-talking parrot of the two — moderate noise, an apartment-plausible footprint, and a bite that measures 61–96 newtons. "Macaw" isn't one bird; it's 11-plus species ranging from a 130-gram Hahn's to a 1,700-gram Hyacinth whose bite was recently measured near 540 newtons, the strongest ever recorded in a bird. Macaws trade the Grey's conversation for color, size and volume most homes aren't built to absorb.</p>
