  <!-- S11 SIZE (direct GSC query, interactive comparator) -->
  <section id="size">
    <h2 class="cag-h2">Which Bird Is Bigger — an African Grey or a Macaw?</h2>
    <p><strong>Quick answer: almost every macaw is bigger, but "almost" is doing real work.</strong> A Congo African Grey runs 400–600 grams; a Timneh runs smaller still. The smallest true macaw, Hahn's, is actually lighter than a Timneh at 130–170 grams — but a Hyacinth Macaw outweighs a Congo Grey by nearly three times, at up to 1,700 grams and 40 inches nose to tail.</p>
    <h3 class="cag-h3">Size &amp; Weight, Side-by-Side — Try the Comparator</h3>
    <p>Pick a macaw species below to see it scaled against a Congo African Grey by weight. The bars are proportional, not to scale in pixels-to-inches, but the ratio is accurate.</p>
