  <!-- S17 SCORECARD -->
  <section id="scorecard">
    <h2 class="cag-h2">Decision Scorecard: African Grey vs Macaw Across 7 Traits</h2>
    <p>Landed here from a "which parrot is better" search? Here's the verdict as numbers — our own 0-to-10 judgment calls from raising Greys and studying macaws closely, kept honest about the columns where the macaw wins outright.</p>
    <a class="inf" href="/african-grey-comparison/"><img class="sec-img inf-img" src="/african-grey-vs-macaw-decision-scorecard.webp" srcset="/african-grey-vs-macaw-decision-scorecard-760.webp 760w, /african-grey-vs-macaw-decision-scorecard.webp 1376w" sizes="(max-width:900px) 92vw, 760px" width="1376" height="768" alt="Decision scorecard rating African Grey and macaw from zero to ten across talking, noise fit, color, beginner suitability, space and safety" loading="lazy"></a>
    <div class="tbl-wrap plain"><table class="score-tbl">
      <thead><tr><th>Trait</th><th>African Grey</th><th>Macaw</th><th>Our note</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>{scores.map((s) => (<tr><td class="sc-trait" data-label="Trait">{s.trait}</td><td class="sc" data-label="African Grey">{s.c}</td><td class="sc" data-label="Macaw">{s.m}</td><td class="sc-note" data-label="Our note">{s.note}</td></tr>))}</tbody>
    </table></div>
    <p>The pattern matters more than the totals: the Grey sweeps talking, apartment fit and space efficiency; the macaw takes visual drama and nothing else contests it. Both columns describe a genuinely good bird — the question is just which trade-off your household can actually live with.</p>
  </section>

